publicis populi Romani litteris monimentisque. All senatus consulta were formally written out and preserved (litteris): a senatus consultum affecting intemational relations was inscribed on two bronze tablets (monimentis), one of which was hung up in the temple of Fides at Rome, the other in a temple of the other nation concerned. Cp. Horace's ‘ monumentum aere perennius?
